.TH "ca8210_test_int_user_read" 9 "ca8210_test_int_user_read" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ca8210_test_int_user_read \- Called by a process in userspace to read a message from the ca8210 drivers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ssize_t" ca8210_test_int_user_read
.BI "(struct file *filp "  ","
.BI "char __user *buf "  ","
.BI "size_t len "  ","
.BI "loff_t *offp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "filp" 12
file interface
.IP "buf" 12
Buffer to write message to
.IP "len" 12
length of message to read (ignored)
.IP "offp" 12
file offset
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If the O_NONBLOCK flag was set when opening the file then this function will
not block, i.e. it will return if the fifo is empty. Otherwise the function
will block, i.e. wait until new data arrives.
.SH "RETURN"
number of bytes read
